column13: Very difficult to communicate with and always hard to get timely responses from.  Very rarely in the hospital.  When responding to questions about procedures she often becomes angry and often doesn't want to be bothered with important issues involving patient care.  She is not approachable and often does not take residents concerns about patient care seriously.
Dr. Baz, the medical director of blood bank at AUB is a very sweet and excellent doctor. She takes care of patients and is involved with other physicians to provide.
Although Dr. Abadjian doesn't work with us anymore, but I always admired his calmness and professionalism with the staff.
NOT APPLICABLE FOR ME, I DIDN'T WORK DIRECTLY WITH DR.ABADJIAN.
I feel honored and privileged to be part of the team under the jurisdiction of Dr George Araj for he is a great mentor and leader.

Dr araj is a father figure in the department, always excited and ready to help the residents in their learning and in their personal lives. He is very generous, his door is open to everyone and he is respected and loved by all the technicians and residents. He loves to work on and involve residents in new research projects, and is always ready to teach residents in lab students.
Sometimes he uses Arabic too much when speaking in the presence of me and he knows I need him to speak English so I can learn properly.

Highly professional,caring for patients, staff , and residents,
trustworthy, father figure of the department.
Dr. Araj is the an excellent medical director of microbiology lab at AUB.

Always dedicated to providing outstanding services to patient care and customers. Also, maintain keenness to updated knowledge in education and fostering research while mentoring Technical Staff, Students, Residents and Fellows in a spirit of collaboration and teamwork including Colleagues.
Needless to mention that my tolerance to aberrant behavior and issues is zero.

Dr. Jessica always seem to have a positive attitude towards everyone. She's very respectful, energetic, and always seem to care about improving her skills. Although she is relatively new in our Pathology department, yet everyone seem to like her and admire her sweet heart.
Dr. Nada is very professional, dedicated to her job. proud to be working under her supervision
Dr. Nada Assaf is professional, respectful, patient caring and her attitude is always positive.
Dr Assaf is very professional, always ready to help and teach residents, very motivated in her section and do a lot of research. She is loved and respected by all technicians and residents.
Very professional and respectful at all times.
– Excellent attending physician, professional, highly involved in academic teaching and research activities.
Dr. Assaf is professional on all levels.

Dr. Shabb is such a role model for being the perfect combination between professionalism and pleasurable. 
Whenever she enters the Lab, she always says Hello to all the staff, nicely enough even if the staff is far in distance. 
She is easy to talk to, very understanding, and treats the staff with friendliness and respect.
Patient safety and quality of result is her first and primary concern.

I always go out of my way to help in any way possible when it comes to patient care with all the limited resources we have especially in terms of staffing.

Always listen to the concerns of physicians and respond to their inquiries with full evidence the soonest possible.

All what I do is to improve patient safety with a professional and collegian atmosphere.
Lovely and one of the most dedicated persons

Dr Daher is very professional and dedicated to quality control in the laboratory. She is always eager to teach the residents wether through daily signout or lectures. She is a role model to the technicians and residents.

Dr. Daher is one of the best. She is the director of the chemistry part which runs always on time, very smoothly, and with exceptional quality. I learned a lot from Dr. Daher during the chemistry rotation. Looking forward to my second.
Highly professional. He is a role–model.
Awarded the GOLD HUMANISM HONOR SOCIETY award in MAY 2023.

I have been working with Dr. Mahfouz for almost 20 years and have not met a professional, dedicated, outstanding, and passionate person about his job as he is.
I am privileged and honoured to have such a remarkable boss.

Dr. Mahfouz has shown great commitment to the growth of the department and to the institution. "He leads by example" and He is always available to support his team and his costumers. Dr. Mahfouz is a valuable asset to this organisation.

Dr Mahfouz is very professional, always ready to help the residents on all levels. He listens to residents concerns and take them into consideration always. He is very dedicated to his work and he is loved by everyone in the department.

Dr. Mahfouz, the medical director of molecular laboratory at AUB is exceptional. He is an amazing teacher as well as an excellent advisor to all of his residents. Rotating in molecular biology, I learned a lot. He is dedicated to providing excellent and meticulous patient care. Add to that, the didactic lectures provided by Dr. Mahfouz are educational and always updating about the latest developments in the field.

Although Dr. Sinno is a relatively new attending doctor, yet she shows great traits. I know Dr. Sinno since she was a resident and she always showed great respect to everyone she worked with. 
A highlight about Dr. Sinno is the fact that she cares a lot about her work down to the smallest details. For instance, if we ever call her to her office, and fail to reach her, she would call again as soon as she sees a call from the Lab. Another example, is that she would come in person to the lab, to ask of us a special request rather than doing it over the phone, ofcourse, always with a smile and thank you phrase.
I consider Dr. Zaatari a role model in professionalism.

Empathy, flexibility, and “problem–solving” skills are 3 essential skills that make him a very good lab director. Dr. Zaher manages unusual, rare, or complex disorders. He leads by example and works on identifying issues and resolving them as quickly as possible. He uses creative problem solving which ultimately leads to promoting a good and positive environment in the lab while giving positive feedback when it's needed. he is a great listener and cares for his team and the team"s growth.

Sometimes, Dr. Chakhachiro treats the staff with disrespect, and undervalue their efforts. In some occasions he uses abusive and rude intimidating language which creates an uncomfortable work environment, and discourages the staff to raise their concerns or inquiries, for fear of retaliation.

On the behavior side, Dr. Chakhachiro, in certain occasions, addresses the staff with disrespect.
In the technical side, sometimes he does not respond to their inquiries timely which ends up by delaying patients' results.
We hardly interact with DR. Baz and she only gave us one lecture over the entire academic year.
Doctor baz is very professional and supportive during our calls.
Dr. Elizabeth is great  at creating a positive workplace, fortifying group work, and decision making for the best patient care environment. It is a great pleasure to have a great director like her.
Professional , helpful, loving, A  father figure to all residents.
The most generous and the best director.

The value, good reputation, credibility and high image and esteem of any institution is based on the features of its community members. The latter necessitates entailing assets such as honesty, fairness, transparency, loyalty, empathy, discipline, positive professional attitude, and shunning away from hypocrisy and appeasement. 
I for one strongly believe, embrace and practice all the afore mentioned at all levels including clinical service, teaching and research, and hope that this should be the practice by all.
Does an effort to keep his residents up to date.

Dr. Kassouf is a true kind spirit. She carries herself with great dignity and also modesty. She exhibits extreme professionalism and always goes above and beyond for the patient. One thing I personally find challenging when working  with Dr. Kassouf is her constant thrive for perfectionism, which would usually turn into observable stress for herself and colleagues around her. However, that is merely a character trait that is coming from a selfless and  altruistic place to provide the most excellent patient–care. Truly an honor to work beside her.

Dr. Assaf is  very wise in character, a hard worker and very knowledgeable as a doctor. 
A leader to follow.
Proud to be part of her team
Very professional , successful , a great addition to the program , always available to teach the residents , come up with research ideas and help residents with all their concerns
Dr. Assaf is very well organized and gives us an excellent series of lectures every year.  She takes a genuine interest in our training and is always supportive.

Very professional, very well established in the field of cytogenetics. Dr. nada is also very puntual, and attends all of our educative activities. She is very involved in the residents learning experiences.

Dr Nada is a very educated,cooperative,respectful,talented director
She is an exceptional doctor and director
This institute needs such doctors that are ambitious ,leaders and loyal
I really admire her

I respect patient privacy 
I treat all caregivers regardless of their job title with respect.
I always arrive ahead of time and respond to inquiries promptly when possible.
I accept constructive comments and suggestions and work on actualizing them.
I communicate directly with all caregivers when warranted for patient care.
Dr. Fakhruddin is a very professional and considerate person. It is always a privilege to work with her.

Dr. Jurdi is very professional, he always gives us useful tips to better our practices in the lab. His intellect shows that he knows much about the technical side of pathology just as much as the medical/theoretical part.
Dr. Nina is the heart and soul of the department. Her presence and aura always light up the laboratory. Very kind and loving person.
I have always been and remain completely dedicated and working to my best abilities day and night to fulfill my professional responsibilities at AUBMC.
Great mentor, always teaching the residents and sharing her experiences specially in her field of expert ‘quality’. Very professional , always available and ready to help.
Dr. Daher is very involved in teaching us how to run our own depratements independently. She is the best in teaching us quality control for the different laboratory tests.
He is highly professional and a LEADER.
Professional, always ready to help residents with academic and non academic concerns. Always pushing the residents forward and ensuring their reaching the required milestones
Dr. Mahfouz is an exemplary professor!

Dr. Mahfouz has an open door policy and is always supportive of our education.  He provides us with a great series of lectures and is an excellent mentor.  When necessary he will provide constructive criticism and follow up on how we handle it.  We are fortunate to have such a caring and professional program director.
Dr. Mahfouz is supportive of all of his residents. Through thick and thin he does an effort to keep us updated and achieve all of our goals.

Dr. Rami Mahfouz is always there when needed. He is available and open to communicate with the team and provide guidance. He is a great motivator. he encourages his team to reach their highest potentials.
Professional with great experience in his field
I always listen. However, if I am not convinced I do not immediately execute, if it is her primary physician  who is  requesting I inquire further.
Dr. Baz is very respectful to all the blood bank staff
Great leader and director; take care of his staff and always ready to help and support.
Highly committed to disciplined, credible, professional, transparent and respectful behavior with empathy, and no tolerance otherwise.
Appreciated and endeared as precious as a family member, blessed to have him as a director.
Sincerely, it is impossible to find a mentor and a director like Dr.  Araj.

Dr. Kassouf is a class act. Her attitude brings light and good spirit to the laboratory. Always smiling and cheerful. 
Way less anxious than I first got to know her and alot more laid back and relaxed. She is immensly helpful and always welcoming to suggestions and improvements.

Dr. Aoun might have the tendancy to drag on with her calls, as opposed to other attendings, for a longer period of time. 
On the other hand, whenever we reach out to her in regards to patient reports and follow ups, she is always helpful and responds immediately to inquiries.
She treats us like fellow colleagues which is something all techs appreciate.
She exudes humor and lightheartedness in her interactions with us.

I take great pride in having the opportunity to work under her guidance. 
Each year, I find myself growing and improving in my skills and knowledge, thank to her expert mentorship, encouraging leadership and support.
Dr. nancy is a great leader

Dr. Najla is everyone's favorite aunt. Always happy, cheerful, kind, warm and lovable. Sometimes she might seem like she has alot on her plate and anxious, but always finds the time to respond and help. Having her in the department is a breath of fresh air.
Dr. Jurdi is everything a tech would want in an attending pathologist: professional, kind, helpful, respectful and warm. The days when he is on call are always smooth and stress–free.

Dr. Shabb truly loves her job and the department and it shows through her energy and spirit. She might seem intimidating to some, however she always finds a way to light up the atmosphere with her witty and charming personality. Although contact with her is less frequent than her counterparts, she is always helpful and responsive.
My workspace is my second home, and the hospital staff are my family. I treat everyone with respect, empathy and care. I am extremely interested and dedicated to my work.

I am always available to discuss and manage any concern / inquiry for all our customers in a respectful and very efficient manner. 

I am a very client focused/dedicated Director who places the patients' and physicians' needs/concerns as my top priority and act accordingly.
Dr Mahfouz is a true leader.

Dr. Mahfouz consistently demonstrates professionalism and respect in all interactions. He is approachable, responsive and always available to support staff and clients. He shows a high commitment to patient care and team development.  His leadership fosters a collaborative environment.
Dr. Sinno is always available and ready to help. She always follows up with the lab. A true professional.

1– I was asked the other day by a staff about the results of a patient. I told that staff that patient results are confidential and that they will be directly shared with the requesting physician and the patient.
2–5–7–8– I mostly deal with Hemato–oncologists. I am sure many such as Dr. D.Noon. Dr. N.Moukalled, Dr. F.Kreidieh, Dr. I.AbouDalle, Dr. Bazarbachi (...etc) would gladly give many examples if asked.
He tends to give sarcastic comments or belittle some staff in front of others. He also gives unprofessional humor, and  sometimes directly criticizes staff unprofessionaly.
